[292.692445, "o", "BsaI-HFv2 Enzyme Information:\r\n======================================================================\r\nRecognition sequence: 5'-GGTCTC-3' / 3'-CCAGAG-5'\r\nCleavage pattern: Cuts 1bp and 5bp downstream\r\nResult: 4bp 5' overhang\r\n\r\nPrimer design strategy:\r\n----------------------------------------------------------------------\r\nForward primer: 5'-GGTCTC-N-[4bp overhang]-[template binding]-3'\r\n  After PCR and digestion: 5'-[4bp overhang]-[amplicon]...\r\n\r\nReverse primer: 5'-GAGACC-N-[4bp overhang RC]-[template binding RC]-3'\r\n  After PCR and digestion: ...[amplicon]-[4bp overhang]-5'\r\n\r\n"]
[292.692736, "o", "The 'N' is a spacer nucleotide between the BsaI site and overhang.\r\nThis is standard practice for Type IIS restriction enzymes.\r\n\r\n======================================================================\r\nValidating primers.fasta format...\r\n======================================================================\r\n"]
[292.692959, "o", "\r\n✓ All format checks passed!\r\n\r\nSummary:\r\n  - 8 primers (4 pairs) designed\r\n  - All primers have correct BsaI sites\r\n  - All binding regions: 15-45bp\r\n  - All Tm values: 58-72°C\r\n  - All primer pairs: ΔTm ≤ 5°C\r\n  - No blank lines in output file\r\n  - Correct header format\r\n\r\n✓ primers.fasta is ready for use!\r\n"]
